						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">LocalH wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, <a href="http://kofler.dot.at/c64/font_01.html" class="postlink">here</a> are a large number of C64 charsets, with varying amounts of character coverage. There are 8x8, 8x16, 16x8, and even a few 16x16 sets included. They're not directly usable on the NES as they're in GIF as well as zipped raw C64 binary (1bpp) so you'll have to re-pixel (or convert from raw binary to NES pattern format) any that you may want to use. Some of the sets also include graphic characters.</div><br />Free tip:<br /><br />You can use YY-CHR to open the 1 bpp images, just make sure to strip out the first two bytes (loading address for C64) with a hex editor first. Then in YY-CHR copy the whole tileset (Ctrl+A, Ctrl+C), change the graphic format to &quot;2BPP NES&quot;, and paste it back (Ctrl+V).</div>

					
